==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monodical
<hw>Mo*nod"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Belonging to a monody.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>For one voice;
monophonic.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Homophonic; -- applied to music in
which the melody is confined to one part, instead of being shared by all
the parts as in the style called <contr>polyphonic</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monodimetric</ent>⟦br⟧
